You don't really need another review of this recipe, but, what the heck -- here is my variation. I skip the prociutto and substitute barbecue sauce which adds to the smoky flavor. I have been making this for years and it is always a favorite at cocktail parties (at which I serve many more formal appetizers!).

Rating: 4
Our local supermarket did not have smoked gouda, so I used regular gouda - it was still very good, but I'd like to try the smoked version. I found the recipe to be a little more time consuming than some have described, but still not too bad. Gouda is a very soft cheese to grate, so you might want to freeze it for a short time to harden it a bit for easier grating. Will definitely make it again for a party or watching a ball game.

