I have made this several times with rave reviews from all (adults and kids too!). At my Christmas party this past year, guests ate them off the cookie sheet before the final oven heating step. At a Super Bowl party over the weekend, I made these (per the request of the party hostess) making a "kids version" substituting the gouda for american cheese, minus the onions. The kids perferred the "adult version" these are so great. What I love about this recipe is that you can make/prepare all the components ahead several days and then just assemble prior to eating. By the way, I brought these to the Super Bowl party, on a foil cookie sheet after the pan browning step. We just popped them in the oven when we were ready for them.

